summary: An Ordinance appropriating the principal sum of ten hundred sixteen and 78/100 ($1016.78) Dollars and Thirty-nine and 50/100 ($39.50) Dollars, interest, or so much of the latter amount as might be necessary out of the General Fund in favor of Keystone Place, Condemnation Fund authorized by Ordinance No. 14029, approved July 17, 1906, providing for the laying off, extending and establishing of Keystone Place in order to provide for the payment of outstanding warrants with interest thereon.
